metadata.name: Boundless Realm of Possibilities #67
metadata.description:
Mesmerizing landscapes, towering mountains to rolling hills, verdant forests to winding rivers, this world is teeming with life and adventure. Keep a watchful eye as you journey across this realm, as you may encounter sea dragons lurking in the depths of the oceans. This map may lead you to the greatest treasure.

's' to save
'a' to see the building animation.
'r' to go back to the full image.

metadata.name: Lands #79
metadata.description:
Lands are a group of artworks creating a minimalist and abstract satellite view. The earth is changing, more and more, day after day, the satellite views are a great proof of that. Stay aware and be careful is important.

I wanted to representing something real, linked with my values, and keep a beautiful composition and colors harmony.  I worked with a new fresh touch for the colors management.

The size, position and frequency of the pieces are generated for each token, along with the color theme. 

Features : 
- piecesCount : the number of circles and rectangles.
- glitchLinesCount :  the number of lines behind the shapes.
- MultipleGlitchDirections : if the directions of the lines behind are just horizontal or vertical, or both (10% of chance to have only one direction) .

 Handmade by code with Javascript, made with fragment.tools
 Quentin Hocdé, Brussels (Belgium), 2023.

metadata.name: Clerestory #59
metadata.description:
Windows welcome daylight, admit fresh air, and offer a view into the outside world. They rarely shatter, always confess the passage of time, and sometimes allow others a chance to look in.

What would the space you're in feel like if it had no windows?

'Clerestory' is an abstract exploration of stained glass windows, drafting shattered sketches for ten potential locations from various perspectives and moments in time. 

Made with WebGL, p5.js, and <3 | CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Canyon #15
metadata.description:
Canyon is a generative art project inspired by canyons and reinterpreted in 9 different styles (that each have their own specificities):
- Grand Canyon
- Radioactive
- Blue Grotto
- Black Crystals
- Magma
- Iceberg
- Imagination
- UV
- Sandstone

Accessories (Kayak, Rowing Boat, Barrels) are present on some variations (in this case, it is possible to generate a second variation without accessories by pressing "a").

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Hybrid Garden #10
metadata.description:
Step into the Hybrid Garden, where the boundaries between art and technology blur to create a mesmerizing landscape of blooming flowers.

This generative project merges AI-generated floral imagery with the power of code, producing a series of unique and captivating compositions.

Explore the beauty of technology-augmented nature and be amazed by the endless possibilities of the Hybrid Garden


Code implemented in javascript with p5.js library
Original images created with AI

metadata.name: Livro #34
metadata.description:
A messy book is a well-read book, a sign of knowledge acquired. It's easy to spot a book that has been loved and used frequently. The pages are bent and creased, the spine is worn, and notes are scribbled in the margins. These imperfections are not a sign of neglect or carelessness, but rather an evidence of a book that has been fully engaged with and understood.
A book that is kept in pristine condition may look nice on a shelf, but it is also a sign that it has not been read as much, or not as deeply. A well-read book is an indication of a curious and active mind, always seeking to learn and grow. So, don't be afraid to let your books get a little messy, it's a sign that you're gaining knowledge and expanding your understanding of the world around you.

Made with p5.js, p5.grain and much love <3
